Ice Cream Style Coding 🍦 (Day 14)
Char Array + Character Conditions (Confidence Focus)
by the way "windows + fullstop" se emojis likh sakto ho

Question 1:
Ek string hai "Ice". Use char array me convert karo aur pehla character print karo.
Hint: s.toCharArray() ka use karo.

Question 2:
String "Lamp" ka last character print karo using charAt() function.

Question 3:
Ek string hai "Milk". Uska second character print karo using array indexing.
Hint: pehle string ko char array me convert karo.

Question 4:
Ek string "Java" ko char array me convert karo aur har character ko ek-ek line me print karo using loop.

Question 5:
String "Code" ka ASCII value print karo for har character.
Hint: (int) ch se ASCII milega.

Question 6:
Check karo kya "Sky" ka pehla character uppercase hai.
Hint: if (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z') se check karo.

Question 7:
String "Tiger" me sirf vowels print karo using loop.
Hint: if (ch == 'a' || ch == 'e' ... )

Question 8:
String "Box" ka har character print karo uska ASCII ke saath. Format: B = 66

Question 9:
Ek string "Cool" lo aur uska second aur third character exchange (swap) karo, fir print karo.

Question 10:
String "data" ke sabhi characters ko uppercase banakar print karo using ASCII logic.
Hint: ch = (char)(ch - 32) ka use karo agar ch lowercase hai.

IUC (If You Can – Practice) 

IUC 1:
String "Hello" ko char array me convert karo aur uska length print karo.

IUC 2:
String "Air" ke characters ko reverse order me print karo.

IUC 3:
String "abc" ke har character ka ASCII value + 1 karke new character print karo.

IUC 4:
String "JAVA" ke last do characters ko alag se print karo.

IUC 5:
Check karo kya "Elephant" ka third character lowercase letter hai.
